In this article, President Biden reflects on his fourth visit to Shanksville, Pennsylvania on the anniversary of the 9/11 attacks. He shares a personal story about a friend who lost his son in the attacks and emphasizes the difficulty of memorializing such tragic events. Biden praises the heroism of the passengers on Flight 93 who fought against the terrorists and discusses the importance of demonstrating that democracies can function in the 21st century. He mentions his conversations with world leaders and the need to bring the country together. Biden also talks about his plans for legislation and the popularity of his policies. He expresses his belief in the uniqueness of the United States and discusses the support he receives from Republicans who want to help. The President also mentions the anniversary of the end of the war in Afghanistan and defends the decision to withdraw troops while acknowledging the criticism of the withdrawal process.